snippet.textDisplay:
@yestheory *my environmental two cents*
.
.
1. Only ever Organic cotton and organic bananas, don't buy ANYTHING with Palm oil 2. Bike/public transportation whenever possible (go down to one car family if you're not already). 3. Your dryer/hot water heater use up the most NRG in your home. Use cold cycles when possible, take shorter showers, and stop using your dryer in lieu of a clothing hanger 4. Stop buying/using plastic baggies replace with reusable options like Pyrex 5. DON'T THROW AWAY FOOD ever. Biggest waste of energy (think about the water it took to grow the food, the gas it took to transport it) 6. *Eat vegetarian one night a week* 7. Do not buy anything from countries with low factory pollution laws. You can find the list online... And Boycott it. Your money speaks volumes.
.
.
.
These are the small steps my husband and I have made in 2020. With you join us? ♥️ Of course there is so much more you can do, but if everyone started towards these simple seven steps... I think it would be a huge impact!!
